Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.27,0:00:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.29,0:00:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.56,0:00:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.32,0:00:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.37,0:01:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.32,0:01:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.68,0:01:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wasted my time winning an obvious victory against the deadbeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.87,0:01:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And my Battle City is over now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.41,0:01:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Yugi, you said, "I won through the power of the card my friend gave me."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.31,0:01:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In that case, I'll entrust you with the card that stands a chance against Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.52,0:01:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no such {\b0}thing{\b1} as miracles!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.55,0:01:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no such {\b0}thing{\b1}\N as the power of a friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.05,0:01:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your {\b0}defeat{\b1}\N will be the proof of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.36,0:01:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So, take this, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.24,0:02:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Final: Yugi VS Malik"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.23,0:02:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Devil's Sanctuary"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.17,0:02:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This card...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.37,0:02:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.27,0:02:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why'd you give it to Yugi...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.31,0:02:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.68,0:02:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Devil's Sanctuary...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.95,0:02:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This card is the only Magic Card that\N can overcome Malik's One Turn Kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.16,0:02:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But then again, you don't even\N {\b0}know{\b1} what the ability Ra has is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.86,0:02:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's see if you can discover\N its secrets and learn how to\N use this card effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right! This will be a {\b0}game{\b1} with\N a mere 20% chance of victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.82,0:02:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi! I believe you said something\N along the lines of winning with\N the power of your friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.29,0:02:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But amidst the heat of battle,\N you can rely on no one other\N than your {\i1}own{\i0} power!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.91,0:02:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card is meant to {\i1}show{\i0} you that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.27,0:02:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}\N actually gave Yugi a card...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think he's up to something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.95,0:02:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:02:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.62,0:02:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably rigged or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.38,0:03:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of {\i1}course{\i0}, it's entirely up to {\i1}you{\i0}\N whether or not you place\N the card in your deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.91,0:03:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll believe in you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll defeat Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.08,0:03:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now we shall commence the\N Battle City Tournament Final Match!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.61,0:03:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik Ishtar versus Yugi Mutou!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.83,0:03:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.34,0:03:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, I don't know what card Kaiba\N gave you, but it's {\i1}useless{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.89,0:03:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will be deemed nothing\N against the almighty Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.78,0:03:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik, I will defeat the evil soul dwelling\N inside of you through this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.26,0:03:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That {\i1}so{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.47,0:03:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That{\i0} I'd like to see you {\i1}try{\i0}!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.14,0:03:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.11,0:03:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to win this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.71,0:03:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's up to you, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.11,0:03:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, it takes three\N sacrifices to Summon a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:03:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi's still at quite a disadvantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.34,0:04:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.55,0:04:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi's got two God Cards now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.10,0:04:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Osiris the Heaven Dragon and\N The Great War God Obelisk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.15,0:04:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Malik's Ra can easily be\N Special Summoned using Resurrection\N of the Dead whenever he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.80,0:04:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Magic Card, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.67,0:04:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Resurrection of the Dead!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.94,0:04:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now behold God!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.74,0:04:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I Summon The Winged Sun Dragon\N of Ra from my Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.01,0:04:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Winged Sun Dragon of Ra\N - Final Form!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}GOD PHOENIX!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.82,0:04:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember my Duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.32,0:04:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used Ra's Special Ability to kill\N every Monster on my field at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.34,0:04:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, they say another hidden ability\N we don't even {\i1}know{\i0} about lies within Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:04:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba said he was able to decipher\N all of Ra's abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.39,0:05:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Could the card he gave Yugi \Nbe a key card needed to beat Ra?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.57,0:05:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will the Duelists please cut and\N shuffle each other's decks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.80,0:05:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shuffle {\i1}thoroughly{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.73,0:05:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And pray Ra sinks to\N the {\i1}bottom{\i0} of the deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.15,0:05:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.24,0:05:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishizu...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.37,0:05:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did lend him a hand,\N just like you asked me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.63,0:05:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was in order to prove that\N there is no such thing as miracles!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That stone slab means {\i1}nothing{\i0} to me.\N It's just a {\i1}relic{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.11,0:05:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Civilizations are built from {\i1}time{\i0} and\N the {\i1}ashes{\i0} of countless people...\N the millions of forgotten dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.26,0:05:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no {\i1}connection{\i0} to someone\N who lived 3,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.96,0:05:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.27,0:05:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They may have been destined for destruction,\N but the {\i1}human spirit{\i0} is eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.41,0:06:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph, if Yugi loses,\N your brother cannot be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.84,0:06:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you sink into\N the depths of despair?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.77,0:06:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe... in Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that the power of friends\N will defeat a god controlled\N by an evil mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.42,0:06:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Miracles {\b0}don't happen{\b1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.96,0:06:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A friend's power is {\b0}powerless{\b1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.85,0:06:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi, your defeat is about\N to be the proof I need!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.65,0:06:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you {\i1}go{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.32,0:06:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, I {\i1}do wonder{\i0} if Ra sunk\N to the bottom of you {\i1}wished{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.75,0:06:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik, your deck already\N knows the answer to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.10,0:06:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has already shown me your defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.65,0:06:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blah, blah, {\i1}blah{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.28,0:06:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Blabber on{\i0} as much as you {\i1}need to{\i0}\N so you have no {\i1}regrets{\i0} when you\N slip away from this realm!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.67,0:06:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Win, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.13,0:06:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You don't gotta\N be afraid of Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.85,0:06:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kick Malik's ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.77,0:06:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm counting on you, Yugi!\N You gotta save Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.16,0:07:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The final fight of Battle City...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.46,0:07:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The fate of the Ishtars...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.51,0:07:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, the fate of us {\b0}all{\b1}\N now lies in your hands, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.48,0:07:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Defeat the evil side of Malik...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.19,0:07:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And regain the key\N to unlock your memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.49,0:07:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And... Please save Malik...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.84,0:07:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I beg of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.90,0:07:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Begin the Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.46,0:07:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I go first!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.01,0:07:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.89,0:07:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The darkness is swallowing\N the entire field...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.24,0:07:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's... a Dark Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.79,0:07:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi... My battle with you\N will be the {\i1}greatest{\i0} Dark Game\N the world has ever {\i1}seen{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.60,0:07:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darkness will cover the {\i1}Earth{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.14,0:07:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the gates of {\i1}Hell{\i0} will open!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.66,0:08:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}now{\i0}, allow me to show\N you something {\i1}nice{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.23,0:08:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.36,0:08:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see the woman?\N The sacrificial offering to the darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.83,0:08:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her life oh so slowly fades away...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.48,0:08:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.82,0:08:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could say {\i1}today{\i0}\N is a festival of darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And shouldn't we pile the\N dinner {\i1}offerings{\i0} together?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.70,0:08:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.87,0:08:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure I already told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.42,0:08:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That I already planned out\N how I wanted to kill you in this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.14,0:08:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll {\i1}show{\i0} you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.69,0:08:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The livestock {\i1}you'll{\i0} be offering!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.04,0:09:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.50,0:09:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.76,0:09:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.22,0:09:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My other self!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.48,0:09:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you can {\i1}see{\i0} him, right...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.03,0:09:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fresh, {\i1}living{\i0} sacrifice\N I've placed on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.79,0:09:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik! What the hell \Nare you trying to pull here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.25,0:09:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my offering will be {\i1}this{\i0} guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.18,0:09:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.61,0:09:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Victory{\i0} or {\i1}defeat{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.32,0:09:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We walk the {\i1}razor-thin line{\i0}\N between them...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.79,0:09:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.92,0:09:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not be {\i1}hasty{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.42,0:09:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll understand in due time!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.51,0:09:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, I'll {\i1}make{\i0} you understand...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.85,0:09:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.89,0:09:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.06,0:09:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon the Swift-Attacking\N Bloodsucking Leech!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.16,0:09:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack the player!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.99,0:09:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.42,0:09:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Swift-Attacking Bloodsucking Leech\N can attack on the turn it's Summoned!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.62,0:10:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The players feel all attacks\N inflicted on their Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.21,0:10:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}look{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.10,0:10:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your sacrifice is devoured\N by the darkness based on the amount\N of Life Points you lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.04,0:10:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment the player's Life hits 0,\N and the sacrifice's body is consumed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The player, too, will be swallowed\N by darkness and suffer\N the ultimate pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.32,0:10:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the rules \Nof this Dark Game, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.58,0:10:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}bastard{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.54,0:10:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahhhh, very {\i1}nice{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.26,0:10:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Writhe in {\i1}pain{\i0}! {\i1}Squirm{\i0}! {\i1}Shout{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.09,0:10:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time you do, pleasure runs \Nthrough my entire body!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.48,0:10:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If my Life Points reach 0, my partner\N will be taken by the darkness...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.29,0:10:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And if I defeat Malik, the {\b0}other{\b1}\N Malik will be the sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.35,0:10:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What do I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.77,0:11:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, we were both chosen\N by the Millennium Items.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the rules state the loser is to\N perish into the oblivion of death!\N It's a fair fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.54,0:11:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I {\b0}jest{\b1}~
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I send your vessel to the darkness,\N you will disappear along {\b0}with{\b1} him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.64,0:11:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But even if {\b0}my{\b1} sacrifice is consumed by\N the darkness, I myself will {\b0}not{\b1} vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.33,0:11:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to fight, other me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.42,0:11:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have to fight this battle\N to find what's important to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.10,0:11:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then I'll fight alongside you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.40,0:11:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.82,0:11:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Defeat Malik's evil heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.20,0:11:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find the light you're searching for!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.92,0:11:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was I who was chosen by\N the Millennium Items!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.22,0:11:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In order to give you strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.19,0:11:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes... Thank you, Partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.24,0:11:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.03,0:11:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's something that\N lies {\b0}beyond{\b1} this battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.67,0:11:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will believe!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.09,0:11:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will defeat this evil being!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.92,0:11:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.01,0:11:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.18,0:11:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Along with Mai and Bakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.14,0:12:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will rescue everyone who's\N fallen to these Dark Games!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.24,0:12:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll find a way to do it\N during this battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.96,0:12:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll save you,\N no matter what it takes...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.97,0:12:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The {\b0}both{\b1} of you!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.19,0:12:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! What kind of \NDark Game has started here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.28,0:12:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi... I don't want you\N to hurt yourself with these\N dangerous games anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.62,0:12:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please don't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.22,0:12:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn's not over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.85,0:12:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Swift-Attacking Bloodsucking Leech\N has another Special Ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By throwing a card out of my hand,\N I can switch it to Defense Mode\N before the turn ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.04,0:12:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another Special Ability beyond\N the power of Swift Attack?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.89,0:12:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...\N Which card should I discard...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.23,0:13:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think I'll pick {\i1}this{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.53,0:13:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can you not sense the terror of\N The Winged Sun Dragon of Ra\N having entered my Graveyard?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.71,0:13:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The moment I draw {\b0}that card{\b1}...\N will be the moment of your deadly defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.15,0:13:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What did he just\N place in the Graveyard...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.65,0:13:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Could it be...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place the Bloodsucking Leech\N in Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.04,0:13:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I set one reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.84,0:13:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.34,0:13:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Damn that Malik.\N What a deadly strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.43,0:13:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If the card he sent to the Graveyard\N using the Bloodsucking Leech\N was in fact the Ra card...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.45,0:13:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...then all he needs is\N Resurrection of the Dead to activate the\N One Turn Kill deadly instant-strike combo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.29,0:13:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.85,0:13:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll Summon this Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.73,0:13:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen's Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.23,0:13:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}King, Queen, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.70,0:13:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One of the three swordsman possessing\N the maximum Speed Summon\N ability for calling God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.27,0:13:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But you're too late!\N {\b0}Far{\b1} too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.68,0:14:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack the Bloodsucking Leech!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.08,0:14:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen's Saber Crush!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.98,0:14:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Bloodsucking Leech was \Nmy {\i1}Defense Monster{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.29,0:14:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Life is {\i1}unaffected{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.12,0:14:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad for {\i1}you{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.45,0:14:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set two reverse cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.13,0:14:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.93,0:14:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.33,0:14:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.37,0:14:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Was it really Ra that he\N sent to the Graveyard?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.71,0:14:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If so, and he draws\N Resurrection of the Dead...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.35,0:14:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I drew a {\i1}nice card{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.42,0:14:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But before I play this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.95,0:14:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to Summon {\i1}another{\i0} Monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.69,0:14:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Juragedo!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.23,0:14:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Juragedo!!\N Obliterate the Queen's Knight!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.08,0:14:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen's Knight's been beheaded!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.20,0:15:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.64,0:15:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.73,0:15:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set two reverse cards\N and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.11,0:15:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card, activate!\N Left Arm Offering!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.39,0:15:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.39,0:15:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. At the cost of placing\N my entire hand in the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.66,0:15:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this card allows me to choose\N one Magic Card from my deck\N and add it to my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.05,0:15:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the card I choose is...\N Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.10,0:15:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!\N Exchange!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.91,0:15:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the card that allows the players\N to exchange a card in their\N hands with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.28,0:15:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now choose!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.72,0:15:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm choosing your\N Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.58,0:15:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.17,0:16:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Malik... You lost\N Resurrection of the Dead so easily...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.73,0:16:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hope you enjoy this to the fullest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.54,0:16:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because with {\b0}this{\b1} reverse card...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.83,0:16:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.14,0:16:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Special Summon Queen's Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.08,0:16:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I Summon King's Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.32,0:16:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the King and the Queen\N are on the field, I can Special Summon\N {\i1}this guy{\i0} as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.89,0:16:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack's Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.68,0:16:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The King...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.94,0:16:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.15,0:16:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Jack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.33,0:16:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "Three Musketeers of Face Cards"\N have been Summoned!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.77,0:16:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you managed to make clever use\N of my Resurrection of the Dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.09,0:16:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I need to do now is draw\N the God Card, and I'll have beaten Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.02,0:16:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Now Yugi's ready to Summon one of his gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.35,0:16:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Malik doesn't have his trump card,\N the Resurrection of the Dead,\N he needs to Summon {\i1}his{\i0} god!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Malik still has some\N reverse cards on the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.52,0:17:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't let his guard down yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.44,0:17:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Malik only has the\N Fusion Cancel card in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.15,0:17:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now's my chance to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.58,0:17:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He doesn't look worried in the least!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.80,0:17:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know you don't have\N the God Card in your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.90,0:17:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter with you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.57,0:17:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be {\i1}scared{\i0} now, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.45,0:17:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and attack me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.58,0:17:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The moment you attack,\N you'll fall prey to God!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.39,0:17:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His face-downs...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.14,0:17:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They must hide a terrible trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.11,0:17:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So your {\b0}fear{\b1}\N saved you for one more turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.01,0:17:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's Yugi thinking up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.93,0:17:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had attacked, he'd probably have been\N able to deal Malik some serious damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.31,0:17:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the feeling!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.18,0:17:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi's Dueling instincts\N probably told him not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.21,0:17:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:18:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may {\i1}look{\i0} like\N Yugi has the upper hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.82,0:18:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it feels like\N Malik's hiding something!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.98,0:18:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn. Draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.36,0:18:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.33,0:18:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, I know you don't have \NGod in your hand right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.05,0:18:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i1}pathetic{\i0} watching you\N wait for a God Card on every\N Draw Phase of your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if the God Card\N you draw just {\i1}happens{\i0} to be\N Osiris the Heaven Dragon...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.75,0:18:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the little amount of cards\N you have in your hand,\N its Attack Power will be weak!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.42,0:18:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So allow me to give you a little {\i1}gift{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.77,0:18:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.69,0:18:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treasure From Heaven!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.49,0:18:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.62,0:18:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now both players are to draw from\N their decks until they hold six cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.92,0:18:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He purposely gave me\N six cards in my hand...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.35,0:18:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! You've been given an opportunity\N to replenish your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.28,0:18:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better not miss God again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.08,0:18:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to {\i1}regret{\i0} this, Malik.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.47,0:19:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then? Did you manage\N to draw your God Card?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.82,0:19:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place Juragedo into\N Defense Position and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.58,0:19:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Battle City rules state that a player\N is only allowed to keep one \NResurrection of the Dead per deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But if you have {\b0}that{\b1} horrible card...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.07,0:19:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.74,0:19:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now I have seven cards in my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I Summon Osiris,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.17,0:19:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}it will have 6000 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.43,0:19:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will he do it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noble Faces, become my sacrifices!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.53,0:19:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon... Osiris the Heaven Dragon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.70,0:20:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've shown yourself, Osiris?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.17,0:20:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Yugi's God Card, \NOsiris the Heaven Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.77,0:20:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It even has 6000 Attack Points! Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.61,0:20:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care {\i1}what{\i0} he's planning!\N It's {\i1}hopeless {\i0}for Malik now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.45,0:20:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.27,0:20:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack him, Osiris!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.94,0:20:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thunder Force!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.12,0:20:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time is right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.25,0:20:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time for {\i1}Ra's power{\i0}, that is!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.71,0:20:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse Magic, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.67,0:20:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revival of the Dark!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.64,0:20:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.93,0:20:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey brother, what's that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.06,0:20:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revival of the Dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.78,0:20:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a card that activates when\N your enemy's Monster attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.70,0:20:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and lets you use a Magic Card from\N your opponent's Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.96,0:20:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that means Malik...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.63,0:20:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can activate\N Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.43,0:20:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, I'll be activating \NResurrection of the Dead \Nfrom the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.65,0:20:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O great Ra whom sleeps in the Earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.57,0:20:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be reborn in the form\N of a mighty phoenix!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.63,0:21:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, my Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.00,0:21:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rise from the Earth\N and dance over the Heavens!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.39,0:21:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Become one with\N the flames of the underworld and\N bear the name of phoenix!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Osiris' Thunder Force was\N absorbed by the God Phoenix!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the turn God rises,\N he possesses the ability of immortality!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.40,0:21:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No attack will work against him!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.62,0:21:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The God Phoenix...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.17,0:21:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The same thing he beat me with!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.76,0:21:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!! I'll burn you to cinders in\N the holy fire {\i1}along{\i0} with Osiris!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.23,0:21:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Resurrection of the Dead, Malik was able to bring The Winged Sun Dragon of Ra onto the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.03,0:22:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi's Osiris' attacks won't work against Ra,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.75,0:22:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's going to be destroyed by God Phoenix's Special Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.43,0:22:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Malik managed to Summon Ra {\i1}again{\i0} on his following turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.73,0:22:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi! Isn't there something you can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.36,0:22:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He set the card he drew on the field without looking at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.33,0:22:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.04,0:22:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Devil's Sanctuary Activates!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.80,0:22:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.44,0:22:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.80,0:22:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.41,0:22:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.48,0:23:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.96,0:23:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.24,0:23:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.14,0:23:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.29,0:23:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.81,0:23:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
